i think id rather die than use strtok, when you give the input count, parsing that list in C becomes as easy as doing this:

using Test 1 and pretending that the ball count exists (called ball_count) you can do...

    for (int i = 0; i < ball_count; i++)
    {
        char letter;
        int num;
        scanf("%c%d ", &letter, &num);
        printf("%c %d\n", letter, num);
    }

which outputs:
N 44
I 23
I 25
B 2
O 69
O 73

which is much easier than using that strtok hazard
